<h1>Problem 971 - 2019 China TST Test 3, P3 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Does there exist a bijection \(f:\mathbb{N}^{+} \rightarrow \mathbb{N}^{+}\), such that there exist a positive integer \(k\), and it&#x27;s possible to have each positive integer colored by one of \(k\) chosen colors, such that for any \(x \neq y\) , \(f(x)+y\) and \(f(y)+x\) are not the same color?</p>
